subject re shaft drives and wheelies from john stafford in article r ja , john r daker wrote:
> > > in a previous article, () says:
> > mike terry asks:
> > >is it possible to do a "wheelie" on a motorcycle with shaft-drive?
> >
> no mike. it is imposible due to the shaft effect. the centripital effects
> of the rotating shaft counteract any tendency for the front wheel to lift
> off the ground. this is true as evinced by the popularity of shaft-drive drag bikes. ====================================================
